        "text": "In the spirit of reusing existing stuff as much as possible: how about... GitHub or GitLab? It would take some creative thinking to reformulate Slack-type exchanges in terms of issues and pull requests, but it might turn out useful. As an example, instead of a message like \"look at this promising stuff I found\" followed by a thread, a pull request adding that site to a list of ressources, with the thread on the pull request. Yes, I know it's not perfect, but it may not be worse than other options, and at least everybody here is probably familiar with it.",
